sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1992005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
introduction Tar chemoreceptor is one of four native chemoreceptors of E.coli, it is mediate chemotaxis response towards aspartate and away from Ni and Co (מקור). This device allows the expression of a functionally native Tar chemoreceptor.
usage and biology This device is very similar to our K1992004 device the only difference is the RBS, here the expression system is using the native RBS of the Tar receptor as found in the E.coli genome (K1992000).
expriments and results In order to test the device it was cloned to chemoreceptor free strain (UU1250) and tested for chemotaxis ability using swarming assay. As can be seen in figure 1 the cells expressing the Tar chemoreceptor create a halo indicating a functional chemotaxis result, which compared to the Tar expression system using a strong RBS(B0034).
Figure 1
Fig1. (a) Tar expression in UU1250 strain cloned with K1992004 expretion system - strong RBS. (b) Tar expression in UU1250 strain cloned with K1992004 expretion system - Tar native RBS
The part was successfully sequenced (fig2) ensuring the present of the promoter, RBS, Tar receptor and terminator.
Figure 2
Fig 2. (a) Sequencing chromatogram of the K1992005 BioBrick- the RBS is marked. (b) The alignment of the sequencing results in compared to the designed sequence - alignment was done using snapgene software.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tzila Davidov,Shilo Ohayon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K777000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part was amplified from genomic DNA of E. coli str. K-12 substr. DH10B chromosome (NC_010473.1).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The transmembrane receptor Tar of E. coli mediates chemotaxis towards aspartate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: One XbaI site was found at position 420. The restriction site was changed from TCTAGt to CCTAGt via QuikChange PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bianca Genenncher

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
